navirus being shipped abroad. [[FEMA]], meanwhile, said the agency \"has not actively encouraged or discouraged U.S. companies from exporting overseas\", and has asked USAID to send back its reserves of protective gear stored in warehouses for use in the U.S.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/03/31/pence-task-force-coronavirus-aid-157806|title=Pence task force freezes coronavirus aid amid backlash|website=Politico}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://theintercept.com/2020/04/01/coronavirus-medical-supplies-export |title=Key Medical Supplies Exported From U.S. to Foreign Buyers |publisher=Theintercept.com |date=2020-04-01 |accessdate=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nPresident Trump stated to reporters: \"This is a pandemic{{nbsp}}... I felt it was a pandemic long before it was called a pandemic.\"<ref name=\"NPR_WHO1\"/>\n\n====March 18====\n\n* Florida: U.S. congressman [[Mario D\u00edaz-Balart]] is one of the first members of Congress to be tested positive for coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/18/politics/mario-diaz-balart-coronavirus/index.html|title=Reps. Mario Diaz-Balart and Ben McAdams become first members of Congress to test positive for coronavirus|first=Paul|last=Leblanc|date=March 18, 2020|website=cnn.com|access-date=March 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321105409/https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/18/politics/mario-diaz-balart-coronavirus/index.html|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Thousands of spring-breakers flock to Florida beaches despite warnings about keeping social distance. The [[Clearwater, Florida|Clearwater City Council]] voted to close down [[Clearwater Beach]] for two weeks, starting March 23 at 6{{nbsp}}a.m. The coronavirus has infected 328 Florida residents and visitors.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/thousands-flock-florida-beaches-ignoring-060744453.html Thousands flock to Florida beaches, ignoring coronavirus concerns] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320221138/https://news.yahoo.com/thousands-flock-florida-beaches-ignoring-060744453.html |date=March 20, 2020 }} by Sophie Lewis, CBS New, 18 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Kentucky: The wife of [[List of mayors of Louisville, Kentucky|Louisville mayor]] [[Greg Fischer]] tested positive for coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.courier-journal.com/story/news/politics/metro-government/2020/03/18/louisville-mayor-greg-fischers-wife-tests-positive-covid-19/2869369001/|title=Louisville Mayor Greg Fischer's wife tests positive for coronavirus, will self-isolate|first=Darcy|last=Costello|website=The Courier-Journal|accessdate=Mar 19, 2020}}</ref>\n* Louisiana: Rev. Tony Spell of Life Tabernacle Church in [[East Baton Rouge Parish]] hosts hundreds at a church service in open defiance of Governor [[John Bel Edwards|John Bel Edwards']] (D) ban against gatherings of more than 50 people.<ref>[https://thehill.com/policy/healthcare/488318-louisiana-church-defies-coronavirus-recommendations-to-hold-service-for-300?fbclid=IwAR3Fy0WDhtRR-_dCFyYFj1nXwqMw1aeImfznyKF5NlxAGjGEZSsIeQjcYXo Louisiana church defies coronavirus recommendations to hold service for 300] BY ZACK BUDRYK, The Hill, 18 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Maryland: The state added 22 more coronavirus cases, to the total of 63 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/maryland-virginia-dc-coronavirus-tuesday-updates/2020/03/17/5f6fa73c-684e-11ea-9923-57073adce27c_story.html|title=Coronavirus cases surge as Northam bans gatherings of more than 10, Hogan postpones primary|last=Chason|first=Rachel|date=18 March 2020|website=Washington Post|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318121502/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/maryland-virginia-dc-coronavirus-tuesday-updates/2020/03/17/5f6fa73c-684e-11ea-9923-57073adce27c_story.html|archive-date=March 18, 2020|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Michigan: The first death from coronavirus in the state is reported, a man in his 50s who had underlying medical 