 Garcetti]] promised that no one will go to jail for violating the [[stay-at-home order]] that goes into effect at midnight. However, a major purpose of the order is to provide enforcement for businesses which are not complying.<ref>\"[https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ L.A. Mayor Promises 'People Aren't Going To Be Marched Into Jail' Under New Safer At Home Order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320200928/https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Dominic Patten, ''Deadline'', March 20, 2020</ref> Marijuana dispensaries are classified \"essential\".<ref>[https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html Marijuana dispensaries are deemed 'essential' in LA, allowed to stay open during coronavirus order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321025617/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html |date=March 21, 2020 }} By Allen Kim, CNN, 20 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Illinois: Governor [[J.B. Pritzker]] issued a stay-at-home order. The order will become effective March 21 and will remain in place until April{{nbsp}}7 but could go longer.<ref>[https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/coronavirus-illinois-issue-stay-home-order-13-million-residents-california-n1164901?fbclid=IwAR0hnei6UFmSAf_aiG9deV6sjuK8LQqcB9T1s8mpqSQHe7WR3ILy0pluCZU Coronavirus: Illinois issues stay-at-home order for 13 million residents] By Minyvonne Burke, NBC News, 20 Mar 2020</ref>\n* New York: Governor [[Andrew Cuomo]] issued a state-wide order that all non-essential workers must stay at home. He noted that the number of coronavirus cases in the state had gone from zero on March{{nbsp}}4 to over 2,900.<ref name=deadline>\"[https://deadline.com/2020/03/new-york-stay-at-home-order-andrew-cuomo-1202888587/ New York Governor Issues Statewide Stay-At-Home Order For All Non-Essential Workers] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320170143/https://deadline.com/2020/03/new-york-stay-at-home-order-andrew-cuomo-1202888587/ |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Erik Pederson, ''Deadline'', March 20, 2020</ref> The same day, Coronavirus cases in New York exceed 7000.<ref name=CNN>\"[https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/20/politics/new-york-workforce-stay-home/index.html] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320204137/https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/20/politics/new-york-workforce-stay-home/index.html |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Veronica Stracqualursi, ''CNN'', March 20, 2020</ref>\n* Michigan: The state reports 225 new cases of coronavirus, bringing the total number of cases there to 549.<ref>{{cite web |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases continue to rise, state total now 549 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/20/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-continue-to-rise-state-total-now-549/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320203728/https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/20/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-continue-to-rise-state-total-now-549/ |archive-date=March 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> A fourth death from coronavirus is reported, a man in his 50s from Oakland County who had underlying health conditions.<ref>{{cite web |title=Officials say Oakland County man is 4th person to die from coronavirus in Michigan |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/21/officials-say-oakland-county-man-is-4th-person-to-die-from-coronavirus-in-michigan/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n* North Carolina: The state activates [[North Carolina National Guard]] to assist in logistics and transportation of medical supplies, as the state reports it has 179 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241363186.html|title=As coronavirus keeps spreading across NC, National Guard activated and citizens stock up|last=Quillin|first=Martha|date=20 March 2020|website=The News & Observer|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320190055/https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241363186.html|archive-date=March 20, 2020|access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: The state reported its first coronavirus death, Mark Wagoner Sr, a 76-year-old attorney from [[Lucas County, Ohio|Lucas County]] in the [[Toledo, Ohio|Toledo]] area.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.10tv.com/article/dewine-says-1st-ohio-coronavirus-death-76-year-old-man-2020-mar|title=DeWine says 1st Ohio coronavirus death is 76-year-old man|date=March 20, 2020|website=10tv.com|access-date=March 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321014412/https://www.10tv.com/article/dewine-says-1st-ohio-coronavirus-death-76-year-old-man-2020-mar|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The state had a total of 169 cases. Governor DeWine announces that senior centers and senior daycare centers will close.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/coronavirus-in-ohio-governor-odh-plan-friday-afternoon-update/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio Friday update: 169 cases, first death confirmed|date=March 20, 2020|website=nbc4i.com|access-date=March 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321015231/https://www.nbc4i.com/community/coronavirus-in-ohio-governor-odh-plan-friday-afternoon-update/|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Tennessee: 15 recovery cases are confirmed in [[Nashville, Tennessee|Nashville]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/health/2020/03/20/coronavirus-nashville-15-patients-have-recovered-virus/2885351001/|title='Encouraging': 15 people in Nashville recovered from coronavirus, health officials say|first=Brett|last=Kelman|website=The Tennessean|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref> However, the health department confirmed the state's first death of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/health/2020/03/20/first-coronavirus-death-tennessee-reported-nashville-davidson-county/2886440001/|title=Nashville health department reports Tennessee's first coronavirus death|first=Emily R.|last=West|website=The Tennessean|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n* Texas: Dallas mega-church preacher [[Robert Jeffress]] agrees to move his Sunday services online.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/coronavirus-fears-force-dallas-megachurch-pastor-jeffress-to-move-services-online-211141698.html Dallas megachurch pastor Jeffress capitulates to coronavirus warnings, moves services online] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320215751/https://news.yahoo.com/coronavirus-fears-force-dallas-megachurch-pastor-jeffress-to-move-services-online-211141698.html |date=March 20, 2020 }} by Alexander Nazaryan, Yahoo News, 20 March 2020</ref>\n* Virginia: Governor Northam activated Virginia National Guard. The state announced they have 114 cases of COVID-19, with 20 hospitalizations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wydaily.com/local-news/2020/03/20/national-guard-activated-james-city-county-coronavirus-positive-cases-jumps-to-19-williamsburg-has-four-the-state-114/|title=National Guard activated: James City County coronavirus positive cases jumps to 19; Williamsburg has four; the state, 114|last=Marsigliano|first=Julia|date=2020-03-20|website=Williamsburg Yorktown Daily|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321020357/https://wydaily.com/local-news/2020/03/20/national-guard-activated-james-city-county-coronavirus-positive-cases-jumps-to-19-williamsburg-has-four-the-state-114/|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====March 21====\n\n* Vice President Mike Pence and his wife test negative for COVID-19 infection.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fox8.com/news/coronavirus/vice-president-mike-pence-and-wife-test-negative-for-covid-19-white-house-says/|title=Vice President Mike Pence and wife test negative for COVID-19, White House says|date=2020-03-22|website=fox8.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* Florida: Governor DeSantis is considering a new strategy to put positive COVID-19 patients into isolation shelters such as abandoned convention centers and hotels instead of returning the patients to their home where they can infect their own family. Cases in Florida reached 763 presumptive positive cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.miamiherald.com/news/coronavirus/article241401496.html|title=DeSantis considers new strategy in Florida coronavirus fight: isolation shelters|last=Mower|first=Lawrence|date=March 21, 2020|website=Miami Herald|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* Michigan: Four more deaths from coronavirus are reported, bringing to total number of deaths in the state to eight.<ref>{{cite web |title=Macomb County officials announce 8th COVID-19 death in Michigan |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/22/watch-live-macomb-county-officials-hold-press-conference-on-coronavirus/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref> Also, the total number of cases of coronavirus in the state rises to 807.<ref>{{cite web |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases continue to rise, state total now 807 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/21/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-continue-to-rise-state-total-now-787/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref> \n* Minnesota: The state confirmed the first death due to the virus; the patient was from Ramsey County and was in their 80's. The patient had contracted the virus from a confirmed case.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.health.state.mn.us/news/pressrel/2020/covid032120.html|title=Health officials confirm first death due to COVID-19 in Minnesota|accessdate= March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: The state has 247 confirmed cases of COVID-19. Facilities providing daycare and assistance for adults with developmental disabilities are closed unless they serve 10 people or less.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ohio's adult day services for developmentally disabled to close as COVID-19 cases rise, 3rd death |url=https://www.fox19.com/2020/03/21/watch-live-gov-mike-dewine-gives-covid-update-after-third-death/ |website=fox19.com|date=March 21, 2020}}</ref>\n* North Carolina: Cases in the state increased to 273. Hospitals in the state begin restricting the visitors to the hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241392921.html|title=North Carolina coronavirus cases rise above 250, as hospitals restrict visitors|last=Shaffer|first=Josh|date=March 21, 2020|website=The News & Observer|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* South Carolina: Governor McMaster orders local law enforcement to disperse crowds on state beaches. Cases in the state grow to 173.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wbtv.com/2020/03/21/additional-coronavirus-cases-south-carolina-statewide-total-rises/|title=46 additional coronavirus cases in South Carolina, statewide total rises to 173|website=[[WBTV]] |language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* Tennessee: The state's second confirmed death due to the coronavirus occurred in [[Nashville, TN|Nashville]]. The man was the brother of Minnesota state Lieutenant Governor [[Peggy Flanagan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wbir.com/article/news/local/tns-second-covid-19-death-was-brother-of-mn-lieutenant-governor/51-73f4f609-68a7-4a49-91b9-e11553ebdc55|title= TN's second COVID-19 death was brother of MN lieutenant governor|accessdate= March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n* Virginia: The state reports it has confirmed 158 total cases in the state.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsls.com/news/virginia/2020/03/21/28-new-coronavirus-cases-in-virginia-now-152-total-cases/|title=35 new coronavirus cases in Virginia, now 158 total cases|last=Smith|first=Samantha|date=2020-03-21|website=WSLS|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\nPresident Trump tweeted about potential coronavirus treatments, specifying Hydroxychloroquine and Azithromycin.<ref name=\"NPR_WHO1\"/>\n\n====March 22====\n\nCoronavirus deaths in the United States stand at 326.<ref name=CNN-March22/>\n* California: Gov. Newsom states that testing should prioritize healthcare workers, hospitalized persons, senior citizens, persons with immune system issues, and other high-risk persons.<ref name=CNN-March22>[https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/22/health/us-coronavirus-wrap-sunday/index.html Some hard-hit areas restrict testing as coronavirus death toll grows in the US], CNN, March 22.</ref>\n* New York: Health authorities recommend health facilities stop testing non-hospitalized patients, in part because of a shortage of PPE (Personal Protective Equipment) for health care workers.<ref name=CNN-March22/> The state had announced initial tests will begin Tuesday, March 22 to see how effective three drugs are against COVID-19. The U.S. FDA (Food and Drug Administration) has shipped 70,000 doses of hydroxychloroquine, 10,000 of Zithromax, and 750,000 doses of [[chloroquine]] to the state.<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2020/03/22/coronavirus-updates-us-state-lockdowns-stimulus-package-congress-pence/2877552001/ Coronavirus live updates: $1,200 checks almost out; NYC mayor says worse is yet to come; Trump offers N. Korea help] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322194345/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2020/03/22/coronavirus-updates-us-state-lockdowns-stimulus-package-congress-pence/2877552001/ |date=March 22, 2020 }}, USA Today, March 22, 2020.</ref>\n* North Carolina: Mecklenburg County announced that they will cover one week cost of people staying in hotels and motels to keep the tenants from being evicted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsoctv.com/news/local/coronavirus-local-updates-positive-cases-nc-continue-rise-total-sits-273/W6AJY5MAWFDL7GCCIEBN7MDQYQ/|title=Coronavirus local updates: Health officials report 80 cases in Mecklenburg Co.|last=Staff|first=WSOCTV com News|website=WSOC|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> The state also confirms a total of 306 cases, and reports that 6,438 tests have been conducted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241402626.html|title=Coronavirus live updates: Here's what to know in North Carolina on March 22|last=Jasper|first=Simone|date=March 22, 2020|website=The News & Observer|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* Ohio: The Ohio Department of Health issues a stay at home order. All non-essential businesses are ordered closed until April 6, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/news/2020/03/read-gov-mike-dewines-stay-at-home-order.html|title=Read Ohio Gov. Mike DeWine's stay-at-home order|first=Laurs|last=Johnston|date=March 22, 2020|website=cleveland.com}}</ref> The state had 351 confirmed cases with 83 hospitalizations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/news/state-news/coronavirus-in-ohio-sunday-update-gov-dewine-dr-amy-acton-to-hold-2pm-updated-on-covid-19-spread/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio Sunday update: 351 confirmed cases; DeWine announces stay-at-home order, daycare changes|date=March 22, 2020|website=nbc4i.com}}</ref> \n* Pennsylvania: [[Montgomery County, Pennsylvania|Montgomery County]] officials announce the first known death from COVID-19 in that county. The statewide total of deaths related to COVID-19 is three.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pennlive.com/news/2020/03/pennsylvania-records-third-death-from-coronavirus.html|title=Pennsylvania records 3rd death from coronavirus|date=2020-03-22|website=pennlive|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n* Washington: President Donald Trump also announces approval of Washington emergency declaration, and have instructed Federal assistance to be given to assist the local recovery efforts in fighting the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/president-donald-j-trump-approves-washington-disaster-declaration-2/|title=President Donald J. Trump Approves Washington Disaster Declaration|website=The White House|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n* West Virginia: Governor Justice urges West Virginians to [[Stay-at-home order|stay home]] as much as possible. 12 cases of COVID-19 are detected in the state.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.newsandsentinel.com/news/local-news/2020/03/justice-not-ready-to-close-west-virginia-as-coronavirus-cases-grow-to-12/|title=Justice not ready to close West Virginia as coronavirus cases grow to 12|last=Adams|first=Steven Allen|date=March 22, 2020|website=[[The Parkersburg News and Sentinel]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* Michigan: An additional death from coronavirus in the state is reported, an older man from Washtenaw County who had underlying medical conditions. The total number of deaths in the state is now nine.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kelly |first1=Dane |title=Washtenaw County officials announce 9th COVID-19 death in Michigan |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/22/washtenaw-county-officials-announce-9th-covid-19-death-in-michigan/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> 258 new cases of coronavirus are reported in the state, bringing the total number of cases to 1,065.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mann |first1=Priya |title=Michigan COVID-19 cases continue to grow |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/michigan/2020/03/23/michigan-covid-19-cases-continue-to-grow/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Virginia: Governor Ralph Northam announces that Virginia Schools are closed for the remainder of the 2019\u20132020 school year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.loudountimes.com/news/gov-northam-closes-schools-for-rest-of-year-tightens-covid/article_2b1db810-6d31-11ea-b037-434531581ed1.html|title=Gov. Northam closes schools for rest of year, tightens COVID-19 preventive measures|first=John Battiston|last=jbattiston@loudountimes.com|website=LoudounTimes.com|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====March 23====\n\n* Michigan: Total number of cases reached 1,328 with 15 deaths. Governor Whitmer issued a stay-at-home order to go into effect at midnight on March 24 and last until April 13.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlive.com/public-interest/2020/03/read-michigan-gov-whitmers-entire-coronavirus-stay-at-home-order.html|title=Read Michigan Gov. Whitmer's entire coronavirus stay-at-home order|date=March 23, 2020|website=mlive|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n* Minnesota: The governor made several announcements regarding the state's response to the virus: a small business loan program would be made available for possibly 5000 businesses during the week for amounts between $2,500 and $35,000, all elective veterinary surgeries would be halted and that he would be revising the budget for the response to the virus asking for an additional $365 million. The state had 235 positive total confirmed cases of the virus and 1{{nbsp}}death.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.mprnews.org/story/2020/03/24/latest-on-covid19-in-minnesota|title= Latest on COVID-19 in Minnesota: Cases rise to 262; 15 currently hospitalized|accessdate= March 24, 2020}}</ref> The governor had also quarantined himself after a member of his security team tested positive for the virus. He claimed to be experiencing no symptoms of the virus. Senator [[Amy Klobuchar]]'s husband was hospitalized due to the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://wxow.com/2020/03/23/mn-gov-walz-to-self-quarantine-after-having-contact-with-person-who-tested-positive-for-covid-19/|title= UPDATE: Walz self-quarantines; Klobuchar's husband hospitalized|accessdate= March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: 442 people in the state have tested positive for COVID-19. 104 people have been hospitalized and six people have died due to the illness. DeWine institutes a hiring freeze for all state government positions except those involved in fighting the virus. The stay at home order signed on March 22 goes into effect at 11:59 PM.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-monday-update-gov-dewine-dr-amy-acton-to-hold-230-briefing/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio Monday update: 442 cases reported, 6 deaths|date=March 23, 2020|website=nbc4i.com}}</ref> DeWine orders a freeze in state hiring for all positions that are not directly related to fighting COVID-19. He also orders a freeze on contract services.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wyso.org/post/coronavirus-ohio-live-coverage|title=Coronavirus In Ohio: March 23|date=March 24, 2020\n|website=wyso.org}}</ref>\n* Oregon: Governor Kat Brown issued a stay at home order, \"to the maximum extent possible\", except for when carrying out essential tasks like getting groceries, refueling their vehicles, or obtaining health care.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.opb.org/news/article/oregon-stay-at-home-order-coronavirus-covid-19-kate-brown/|title=Gov. Kate Brown Issues Order Directing Oregonians To 'Stay Home'|first=Dirk|last=VanderHart|website=www.opb.org}}</ref>\n* [[Diamond Comic Distributors]] announce they are no longer accepting new stock or distributing new comics until further notice. Because they're the exclusive distributor, that means all comic books would have to postpone publication of future issues after the titles released on 25 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsarama.com/49539-diamond-steve-geppi-officially-announce-explain-shutdown.html|title=DIAMOND, STEVE GEPPI Officially Announce, Explain Pause In Distribution|website=Newsarama}}</ref>\n\nWHO Director-General Tedros said \"Using untested medicines without the right evidence could raise false hope and do more harm than good.\" He also described the pandemic as \"accelerating\".<ref name=\"NPR_WHO1\"/>\n\n====March 24====\n\n* Minnesota: The state announces a total of 262 confirmed cases of the virus in the state. Twenty-two of those cases require hospitalization and there is 1{{nbsp}}confirmed death. There are 15 people hospitalized and 88 patients who had required isolation no longer do.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.health.state.mn.us/diseases/coronavirus/situation.html|title= Situation Update for Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19)|accessdate= March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: The state has 564 confirmed COVID-19 cases: 145 hospitalizations and 8{{nbsp}}deaths.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://myfox28columbus.com/news/local/march-24-coronavirus-in-ohio-update|title= Coronavirus cases rise to 564 with 8 deaths in Ohio|date= March 24, 2020|website=myfox28columbus.com}}</ref>\n* Rhode Island: Governor [[Gina Raimondo]] announces that there are 124 confirmed cases of the virus. She claims that \"many, many\" have recovered.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wpri.com/health/coronavirus/march-24-coronavirus-update/|title= 18 new cases of COVID-19 in RI; Raimondo offers child care options|accessdate= March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n* South Carolina: Governor [[Henry McMaster]] as well as South Carolina Superintendent of Education Molly Spearman announce that K-12 schools statewide will remain closed through the month of April in order to prevent the spread of the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Thomas |first1=Elizabeth |title=South Carolina schools to be closed through April |url=https://wpde.com/news/coronavirus/south-carolina-schools-to-be-closed-through-april |publisher=[[WPDE]] |accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Michigan: The death toll from coronavirus in the state reaches 24, and the total number of cases climbs to 1,791.<ref>{{cite web |title=Michigan reaches 1,791 confirmed coronavirus (COVID-19) cases, 24 deaths |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/24/michigan-reaches-1791-confirmed-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-state-reports/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n====March 25====\n\nSenate Republicans and Democrats strike a deal on a version of the stimulus bill which includes: providing $1,200 to most adults (phased out for persons making from $75,000 to $99,000 a year), $600 a week unemployment benefits (approximately $2,400 a month) on top of state unemployment benefits and to last potentially for four months and including freelancers and other workers in the \"gig economy\", and $500 billion for businesses and municipalities. This last part is to be overseen by an inspector general in the Treasury Department and a Congressional Oversight panel.<ref name=\"Vox, $2 Trillion stimulus, March 25\">[https://www.vox.com/2020/3/25/21192716/senate-deal-coronavirus-stimulus The Senate has struck a $2 trillion deal on the coronavirus stimulus. Here's what's in it.] Vox, Ella Nilsen and Ali Zhou, March 25, 2020.</ref>\n* Alaska: Governor Dunleavy orders everyone arriving in Alaska to self-quarantine for 14 days upon arrival, effective March 25, with limited exceptions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gov.alaska.gov/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/03232020-SOA-COVID-19-Health-Mandate-010.pdf|title=COVID-19 Health Mandate|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Mazzei|first1=Patricia|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/25/us/coronavirus-united-states.html|title=Governors Tell Outsiders From 'Hot Zone' to Stay Away as Virus Divides States|date=25 March 2020|work=The New York Times|accessdate=25 March 2020|last2=Bosman|first2=Julie|last3=Bogel-Burroughs|first3=Nicholas}}</ref>\n* Michigan: The number of deaths from coronavirus increases to 43, while 507 new cases are reported. This brings the total number of cases in the state to 2,294.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Haddad |first1=Ken |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases total 2,294; Death toll rises to 43 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/25/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-total-2295-death-toll-rises-to-43/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio. As of 2:00 pm, there are 704 confirmed cases of COVID-19, with 182 resulting in hospitalization (including 75 ICU admissions). Ten people have died from the virus. Though 704 cases have been confirmed in the state, the actual number of cases is believed to be much higher.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-wednesday-update-gov-dewine-dr-amy-acton-plan-2pm-briefing/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio update: 704 cases reported, 10 deaths|date=March 25, 2020|website=nbc4i.com}}</ref> The Ohio General Assembly passes House Bill 197, which does many things, such as extending primary voting to April 28 and banning water utilities from disconnecting service.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/open/2020/03/ohio-senate-passes-coronavirus-relief-bill-extending-primary-voting-until-april-28-waiving-school-testing-requirements.html|title=Ohio legislature passes coronavirus relief bill extending primary voting until April 28, waiving school testing requirements|first1=Jeremy|last1=Pelzer|first2=Andrew|last2=Tobias|website=cleveland.com|date=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====March 26====\n\n* United States: the total number of reported confirmed cases in the United States surpasses that of China with over 85,000, making it the country with the highest number of coronavirus patients, in the world.<ref name=\"SA-20200326\">{{cite news |last1=Berke |first1=Jeremy |last2=McFall-Johnsen |first2=Morgan |title=USA Now Has More COVID-19 Cases Than Any Other Country in The World |url=https://www.sciencealert.com/usa-is-now-the-centre-of-the-covid-19-outbreak-as-their-case-numbers-top-italy-s |date=26 March 2020 |work=ScienceAlert.com |accessdate=27 March 2020 }}</ref><ref name=\"NYT-20200326\">{{cite news |last=McNeil, Jr. |first=Donald G. |title=The U.S. Now Leads the World in Confirmed Coronavirus Cases\u2014Following a series of missteps, the nation is now the epicenter of the pandemic. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/26/health/usa-coronavirus-cases.html |date=26 March 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=27 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52056586 Coronavirus: US overtakes China with most cases], BBC, March 27, 2020</ref>\n* Michigan: 17 additional deaths from coronavirus are reported, bringing the total number of deaths in the state to 60. The total number of cases in the state increases to 2,856.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hutchinson |first1=Derick |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases total 2,856; Death toll rises to 60 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/26/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-total-2856-death-toll-rises-to-60/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: Ohio has 867 confirmed COVID-19 cases, with 223 of those cases resulting in hospitalization and 15 resulting in death.<ref name=\"Business Journal OH PA\">{{cite web|title=Coronavirus Cases Update: March 26, 2020|url=https://businessjournaldaily.com/coronavirus-cases-update-march-26-2020/|website=businessjournaldaily.com|date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n* Pennsylvania. The state had 1,687 confirmed cases.<ref name=\"Business Journal OH PA\"/>\n* New York: Trump announces that USNS ''Comfort'' will be heading up to New York City to assist local hospitals. The ship is scheduled to depart on 28 March and scheduled to arrive in New York City on 30 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/trump-says-usns-comfort-worlds-biggest-hospital-ship-will-embark-to-nyc-to-treat-coronavirus|title=Trump says USNS Comfort, world's biggest hospital ship, will embark to NYC to treat coronavirus|last=O'Reilly|first=Andrew|date=2020-03-26|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> Cuomo announces the state will allow two patients to share one ventilator.<ref>{{cite news|author=Dakin Andone|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/26/health/splitting-ventilators-coronavirus/index.html|title=New York will allow two patients to share a single ventilator|date=March 26, 2020|work=CNN}}</ref>\n\n====March 27====\n\n* Michigan: The number of deaths of coronavirus in the state increases to 92, while the total number of cases climbs to 3,657.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ainsworth |first1=Amber |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases up to 3,657; Death toll now at 92 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/27/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-up-to-3657-death-toll-now-at-92/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: 1,137 people in Ohio have the virus, with 276 needing hospitalization. 19 COVID-19 patients have died.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abc6onyourside.com/news/local/march-27-coronavirus-in-ohio-update|title=Coronavirus claims the lives of 19 in Ohio as 1137 infected|date= March 27, 2020|website=abc6onyourside.com}}</ref> DeWine signs House Bill 197, which extends the primary election through April 28, bans water disconnections, waives standardized testing requirements for public schools, and extends the state income tax filing and payment deadline to July 15.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/open/2020/03/ohio-coronavirus-cases-surpass-1000-mark-with-19-deaths-gov-mike-dewines-friday-march-27-briefing.html|title=Ohio coronavirus cases surpass 1,000 mark with 19 deaths: Gov. Mike DeWine's Friday, March 27 briefing|first=Laura|last=Hancock|date=March 27, 2020\n|website=cleveland.com}}</ref>\n* Colorado: The 8pm Denver Howl is started by folks in a neighborhood near the now closed [[Denver Botanic Gardens]] and [[Denver Zoo]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://theknow.denverpost.com/2020/04/07/denver-howling-every-night-8-pm/236985/|title=Why you keep hearing howling at 8 p.m. across Denver|date=April 7, 2020|website=The Know}}</ref>\n\nA survey of more than forty leading economists by the [[University of Chicago]] published on March 27 indicated that prematurely ending lockdowns (e.g., business closures) would do more economic harm than good. Specifically, none of the economists surveyed disagreed with the statement that: \"Abandoning severe lockdowns at a time when the likelihood of a resurgence in infections remains high will lead to greater total economic damage than sustaining the lockdowns to eliminate the resurgence risk.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.igmchicago.org/surveys/policy-for-the-covid-19-crisis/|title=Policy for the COVID-19 Crisis|work=igmchicago.org|date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\nPresident Trump signs the [[Coronavirus Aid, Relief, and Economic Security Act]] into law on March 27.\n\n====March 28====\n\n* Michigan: President Donald Trump approves the state's disaster declaration.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McDonald |first1=Mara |title=President Trump approves Disaster Declaration for state of Michigan |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/28/president-trump-approves-disaster-declaration-for-state-of-michigan/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Meanwhile, the state's total cases of coronavirus increased to 4,658 while the death toll climbed to 111.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dado |first1=Natasha |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases total 4,658; Death toll rises to 111 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/28/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-total-4650-death-toll-rises-to-111/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: According to the [[Ohio Department of Health]], the state has 1,406 cases of COVID-19, 344 of which resulted in hospitalization and 25 of which resulted in death.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news5cleveland.com/news/continuing-coverage/coronavirus/there-are-now-1406-confirmed-covid-19-cases-in-ohio-25-deaths|title=There are now 1406 confirmed COVID-19 cases in Ohio, 25 deaths|first=Drew|last=Scofield|date=March 28, 2020|website=news5cleveland.com}}</ref> Ohio Department of Health director Amy Acton reports that the virus's peak is expected in mid-May and that during that peak, there could be up to 10,000 cases a day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.10tv.com/article/dr-amy-acton-ohioans-we-are-flattening-curve-2020-mar|title=Dr. Amy Acton to Ohioans: \"We are flattening the curve\"\n|date=March 28, 2020|website=10tv.com}}</ref> DeWine asks the [[FDA]] to issue an emergency waiver for the use of new technology that can sterilize face masks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abc6onyourside.com/news/local/march-28-coronavirus-in-ohio-update|title=Ohio confirms 1,406 coronavirus cases, Governor DeWine makes plea to FDA|date=March 28, 2020\n|website=abc6onyourside.com}}</ref>\n\n====March 29====\n\nAdmiral [[Brett Giroir]] of the [[United States Public Health Service Commissioned Corps|United States Public Health Service]] reports, at the President's Sunday press conference, that the total of US testing for the virus is 894K.<ref>YouTube. PBS channel. (29 March 2020). \"WATCH LIVE: Trump and White House Coronavirus Task Force hold briefing\". [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PlyZMGIntGY PBS channel on YouTube] Retrieved 29 March 2020.</ref>\n* Michigan: State Representative [[Isaac Robinson (politician)|Isaac Robinson]] passes away of suspected coronavirus at the age of 44.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kelly |first1=Dane |title=Michigan state Rep. Isaac Robinson dies |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/30/michigan-state-rep-isaac-robinson-dies/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref> Meanwhile, the state's total number of coronavirus cases increases to 5,524 with 132 deaths.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dado |first1=Natasha |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases total 5,524; Death toll rises to 132 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/29/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-total-5486-death-toll-rises-to-132/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: The state has 1,653 cases with 403 hospitalizations including 139 ICU admissions, and 29 deaths.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.10tv.com/article/ohio-confirms-first-coronavirus-cases-continues-testing-2020-mar|title=1,653 confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Ohio; 29 deaths and 403 hospitalized|date=March 29, 2020|website=10tv.com}}</ref>\n\n====March 30====\n\n* Michigan: 52 more deaths from coronavirus are reported, bringing the death toll in the state to 184. The total number of cases in the state rises to 6,498.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hutchinson |first1=Derick |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases up to 6,498; Death toll now at 184 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/30/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-up-to-6498-death-toll-now-at-184/ |website=clickondetroit.com |date=March 30, 2020 |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: Ohio had 1,933 cases of COVID-19, including 475 that resulted in hospitalization and 39 that resulted in death. Governor DeWine extended the closure of schools to May 1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-monday-update-health-department-to-release-latest-covid-19-case-numbers/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio update: 1,933 cases reported, 39 deaths, K-12 school order extended|date=March 30, 2020|website=nbc4i.com}}</ref>\n\n====March 31====\n\n* Georgia: Georgia Governor [[Brian Kemp]] suspends in class instruction for all Georgia public schools for the remainder of the 2019\u20132020 school year. Students will continue their education through online formats.\n* Michigan: The number of cases of coronavirus in the state reaches 7,615 and the death toll increases to 259.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hutchinson |first1=Derick |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases up to 7,615; Death toll rises to 259 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/31/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-up-to-7615-death-toll-rises-to-259/ |website=clickondetroit.com |date=March 31, 2020 |accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: Ohio has 2,199 cases of the virus. 585 of those cases resulted in hospitalization and 55 resulted in death. Governor DeWine announces an order requiring that organizations with ventilators or similar devices report them to the state.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-tuesday-update-2-p-m-briefing-with-gov-dewine-dr-acton-scheduled/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio Tuesday update: 2,199 cases reported, 55 deaths|date=March 31, 2020|website=nbc4i.com}}</ref> President Trump approves the state's Disaster Declaration.<ref>{{cite press|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/president-donald-j-trump-approves-ohio-disaster-declaration-3/|date= March 31, 2020 |title=President Donald J. Trump Approves Ohio Disaster Declaration|publisher=whitehouse.gov}}</ref>\n\n====Testing status at end of March====\n\nThe NYT reported on March 28 that despite significant improvement in testing capacity in the U.S., \"hospitals and clinics across the country still must deny tests to those with milder symptoms, trying to save them for the most serious cases, and they often must wait a week for results.\" Mr. Trump asked the South Korean president for as many kits as possible from the 100,000 produced daily there. However, \"having the ability to diagnose the disease three months after it was first disclosed by China does little to address why the United States was unable to do so sooner, when it might have helped reduce the toll of the pandemic.\" One expert indicated the delay of testing adversely impacted other aspects of the coronavirus response.<ref name=\"NYT_Response1\"/> ''Vox'' reported that during the week of March 25 to April 1, the U.S. was \"performing about 110,000 tests per day\". Several experts estimated that between 500,000 to \"millions\" of tests per day are necessary. There are many challenges to ramping up capacity: \"Complaints vary, but labs say they don't have enough swabs, test kits, reagents, personal protective equipment (PPE), staff, or machines to run the specific tests required.\" Money and regulations are also challenges.<ref name=\"Vox_Test1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/2020/4/15/21222375/coronavirus-covid-19-test-update-end-social-distancing|title=America's embarrassingly mediocre coronavirus testing, in 2 charts|via=vox.com}}</ref>\n\n===April===\n====April 1====\n\n* Michigan: The death toll from coronavirus increases to 337, while the total number of cases climbs to 9,334.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ainsworth |first1=Amber |title=Coronavirus in Michigan: Here's where we stand today |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/michigan/2020/04/02/coronavirus-in-michigan-heres-where-we-stand-as-of-wednesday-night/ |website=clickondetroit.com |date=April 2, 2020 |accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: There are 2,547 confirmed cases. 679 people have been hospitalized because of the virus and 65 have died from it. Governor DeWine announced during his daily press conference that there is a new method to divide the state into hospital capacity regions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-wednesday-update-gov-dewine-to-hold-2-p-m-briefing/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio update: 2,547 cases, 65 deaths reported|date=April 1, 2020|website=nbc4i.com}}</ref>\n\n====April 2====\n\n* Indiana: Superintendent of Public Instruction [[Jennifer McCormick]] directs that Indiana schools will close for the rest of the academic year, and continue providing instruction remotely.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indystar.com/amp/5110846002|title=The Indianapolis Star}}</ref>\n* Michigan: Gov. Whitmer officially closes schools in the state for the rest of the 2019\u201320 school year.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hutchinson |first1=Derick |title=Michigan K-12 schools closed for rest of school year\u2014what we know |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/04/02/michigan-k-12-schools-closed-for-rest-of-school-year-what-we-know/ |website=clickondetroit.com |date=April 2, 2020 |accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref> Meanwhile, total cases of coronavirus in the state increase to 10,791 with a death toll of 417.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hutchinson |first1=Derick |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases up to 10,791; Death toll now at 417 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/04/02/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-up-to-10791-death-toll-now-at-417/ |website=clickondetroit.com |date=April 2, 2020 |accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: Gov. There are 2,902 confirmed cases with 802 of them leading to hospitalization and 81 leading to death.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-thursday-update-gov-dewine-dr-acton-to-hold-daily-2pm-news-conference/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio update: 2,902 confirmed cases, 81 deaths, 'Stay at Home' order extended|date=April 2, 2020|website=nbc4i.com}}</ref> Dewine extends the Ohio's stay at home order through May 1st with new restrictions: campgrounds must close, all retail businesses must post signs limiting how many people are allowed in at one time, and wedding receptions are limited to 10 people. The order also establishes a state board to evaluate what is and is not an essential business.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wlwt.com/article/here-s-what-s-new-about-ohio-s-extended-stay-at-home-order/32021704|title=Here's what's new about Ohio's extended stay-at-home order|website=wlwt.com}}</ref>\n\n====April 3====\n\n[[File:PA National Guard, April 2020.jpg|thumb|[[Pennsylvania National Guard]]smen unload cots at a [[Federal Emergency Management Agency|FEMA]] field hospital at [[Temple University]] on April 3.]]\n\n* Indiana: Governor [[Eric Holcomb]] announces a two-week extension of Indiana's stay-at-home order. The new order will run through April 20.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wthr.com/article/indiana-coronavirus-updates-gov-holcomb-extends-stay-home-order-2-weeks |title=Indiana coronavirus updates for Friday, April 3, 2020\u2014Health News 13 WTHR Indianapolis |publisher=Wthr.com |date= April 3, 2020|accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n* Michigan: 1,953 new cases of coronavirus are reported, bringing the total number in the state to 12,744 with a death toll of 479.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hutchinson |first1=Derick |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases up to 12,744; Death toll now at 479 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/04/03/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-up-to-12744-death-toll-now-at-479/ |website=clickondetroit.com |date=April 3, 2020 |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: The state has 3,312 confirmed cases with 895 of them leading to hospitalization and 91 leading to death.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-friday-update-gov-dewine-schedules-2pm-briefing-on-covid-19-in-the-state/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio Friday update: 3,312 confirmed cases and 91 deaths|date=April 3, 2020|website=nbc4i.com}}</ref>\n\n====April 4====\n\n* Alabama: Governor [[Kay Ivey]] announces a stay-at-home order through April 30. Attorney General Steve Marshall said the order can be enforced criminally, but he said he hopes it will not come to that. Disobeying the order is a Class C misdemeanor that can carry a $500 penalty.<ref>{{cite web|author=2 days ago |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/politics/watch-live-gov-ivey-holding-joint-press-conference-on-alabamas-covid-19-fight/ar-BB128Ocq |title=Gov. Ivey issues stay-at-home order for Alabama |publisher=Msn.com |date=2017-05-31 |accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n* Michigan: The total cases of coronavirus in the state increase to 14,225 with a death toll of 540.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kelly |first1=Dane |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases up to 14,225; Death toll now at 540 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/04/04/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-up-to-14225-death-toll-now-at-540/ |website=clickondetroit.com}}</ref>\n* Ohio: There are 3,739 total cases including 1,006 that resulted in hospitalization and 102 that resulted in death. DeWine signs an executive order removing training requirements for mental health and marriage counselors to make telehealth visits more easily accessible.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abc6onyourside.com/news/local/april-4-coronavirus-in-ohio-update|title=Ohio confirms over 100 coronavirus deaths, at least 1,000 hospitalized|first=Sarah|last=Wynn|date=April 4, 2020|website=abc6onyourside.com}}</ref>\n\n====April 5====\n\n* Indiana: Total coronavirus cases reaches 4,411 in the state and the death toll reaches 127.<ref name=\"worldometers1\">{{Cite web | url=https://worldometers.info/coronavirus/country/us/ |title = United States Coronavirus: 418,572 Cases and 14,241 Deaths\u2014Worldometer}}</ref>\n* Michigan: The total number of cases of coronavirus in the state increase to 15,718 with a death toll of 617.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kelly |first1=Dane |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases up to 15,718; Death toll now at 617 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/04/05/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-up-to-15718-death-toll-now-at-617/ |website=clickondetroit.com |date=April 5, 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: There are 4,043 confirmed cases.<ref name=\"Business Jounral OH PA Ap 5\">{{Cite web|url=https://businessjournaldaily.com/coronavirus-case-update-april-5-2020/|title=Coronavirus Case Update: April 5, 2020|date=April 5, 2020|website=businessjournaldaily.com}}</ref>\n* Pennsylvania: The state has 11,510 cases. 1,072 lead to hospitalization and 150 lead to death.<ref name=\"Business Jounral OH PA Ap 5\"/>\n\n====April 6====\n\n* Indiana: The state's number of coronavirus cases increases to 4,944 with 139 deaths.<ref name=\"worldometers1\"/>\n* Michigan: The total number of cases of coronavirus in the state increase to 17,221 with a death toll of 727.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hutchinson |first1=Derick |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases reach 17,221; Death toll up to 727 |url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Timeline_of_the_2020_coronavirus_pandemi