rd Burr]] (R-NC) allegedly used his position as chairman of the [[United States Senate Select Committee on Intelligence|Senate Intelligence Committee]] to mislead the public about COVID-19. He personally made between $582,029 and $1.56 million by selling off stock days before the market crashed.<ref>[https://www.npr.org/2020/03/19/818192535/burr-recording-sparks-questions-about-private-comments-on-covid-19?fbclid=IwAR3ay5WjYSiEljFT7F2pnXfJVfP2i4h7jvyAe_UXwzJ_1SD_2SCFQbOoqQw Intelligence Chairman Raised Virus Alarms Weeks Ago, Secret Recording Shows] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320033836/https://www.npr.org/2020/03/19/818192535/burr-recording-sparks-questions-about-private-comments-on-covid-19%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR3ay5WjYSiEljFT7F2pnXfJVfP2i4h7jvyAe_UXwzJ_1SD_2SCFQbOoqQw |date=March 20, 2020 }} by Tim Mak, NPR, 19 March 2020</ref><ref>[https://thehill.com/homenews/senate/488545-burr-sold-off-significant-amount-of-stock-a-week-before-market-crash-started?fbclid=IwAR3CLqLDL5B0PnvUBEwMqqy_ZIkzBDtWCxILzrD0Tn-6jadjRXkiT6gKnhE Burr sold off significant amount of stock a week before market crash started: report] BY MARTY JOHNSON, The Hill, 19 Mar 2020</ref> Police in [[Guilford County, North Carolina]] stopped a truck with nine tons of stolen toilet paper.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/police-north-carolina-stopped-truck-003300973.html Police in North Carolina stopped a truck with 18,000 pounds of stolen toilet paper] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320220428/https://news.yahoo.com/police-north-carolina-stopped-truck-003300973.html |date=March 20, 2020 }} by Rosie Perper, INSIDER, 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Ohio: The state has 119 cases of COVID-19 resulting in 33 hospitalizations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-thursday-update-governer-odh-to-give-afternoon-update-on-covid-19/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio Thursday update: 119 confirmed cases in the state|date=March 19, 2020|website=nbc4i.com|