&category=473|publisher=[[Badminton World Federation]]|accessdate=4 February 2016}}</ref>\n\t|2009; |255\n\t|2010; |151\n\t|2011; |31\n\t|2012; |19\n\t|2013; |11\n\t|2014; |11\n\t|2015; |12\n        |2016; |6\n        |2017; |3\n|2018; |3\n|2019; |6\n|2020; |\n| \n|\n|}\n\n===Summer Olympics===\n====2016 Summer Olympics====\n{{See also|Badminton at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's singles}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Stage\n! Opponent\n! Result\n! Games\n! Points\n|-\n| Group stage (Round 1)\n| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Laura S\u00e1rosi]]|HUN|2016 Summer}}\n| {{Won}}\n| 2\u20130\n| 21\u20138, 21\u20139\n|-\n| Group stage (Round 3)\n| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Michelle Li (badminton)|Michelle Li]]|CAN|2016 Summer}}\n| {{Won}}\n| 2\u20131\n| 19\u201321, 21\u201315, 21\u201317\n|-\n| Pre-Quarterfinals\n| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Tai Tzu-ying]]|TPE|2016 Summer}}\n| {{Won}}\n| 2\u20130\n| 21\u201313, 21\u201315\n|-\n| Quarterfinals\n| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Wang Yihan]]|CHN|2016 Summer}}\n| {{Won}}\n| 2\u20130\n| 22\u201320, 21\u201319\n|-\n| Semifinals\n| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Nozomi Okuhara]]|JPN|2016 Summer}}\n| {{Won}}\n| 2\u20130\n| 21\u201319, 21\u201310\n|-\n| Final\n| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Carolina Mar\u00edn]]|ESP|2016 Summer}}\n| {{Lost}}\n| 1\u20132\n| 21\u201319, 12\u201321, 15\u201321\n{{col-end}}\n\n== Record against selected opponents ==\nRecord against Year-end Finals finalists, World Championships semi-finalists, and Olympic quarter-finalists. Accurate as of [[2020 All England Open|13 March 2020]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://bwfbadminton.com/player/73173/pusarla-v-sindhu/head-to-head-analysis |title=PUSARLA V. Sindhu &#124; HEAD TO HEAD ANALYSIS &#124; Profile |website=bwfbadminton.com |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center; font-size:small\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Players\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Matches\n! colspan=\"2\" | Results\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Change\n|-\n! Won\n! Lost\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{fla